# pC offline analysis package

Some key directories:
DATA 
  /dev/sda1/data 
  /dev/sdb1/data
  /dev/sdc1/data
  symboric link to: /usr/local/cnipol/data

ONLINE LOG
  /dev/sda1/log
  /dev/sdb1/log
  /dev/sdc1/log
  symboric link to: /usr/local/cnipol/log

ANALYSIS
  cnipol

SRC
  cnipol/src
	AsymMain.cc    "main program. hundle options"
	AsymRead.cc    "read in raw data and decode"
	AsymRunDB.cc   "read in condistions for runs from run.db" 
	AsymHbook.cc   "histogram booking"
	hb_lib.f       "utility library to call hbook from c++"
	AsymProcess.cc "event looop processing program"
   	AsymCalc.cc    "end of run routine"
	RunDBReader.cc "portable RunDB read program"

	Asym.h
	AsymMain.h
	rpoldata.h
	rhicpol.h
	WeightedMean.h
		
  Executable : 
	Asym          "Modified asymrhic. Current version"
	RunDBReader   "portable run.db reader/printer"


Set up for running Asym"

1. Environmental variables (in bash format)

        export INSTALLDIR=/usr/local/cnipol
        export CONFDIR=$INSTALLDIR/config
        export CALIBDIR=$INSTALLDIR/calib
        export ONLINEDIR=$INSTALLDIR
        export ONLINELOGDIR=$ONLINEDIR/log
        export DATADIR=$ONLINEDIR/data
        export ASYMDIR=$HOME/2005/offline/asym

	#whereever executable to be installed.
        export PATH=$HOME/bin:$PATH


2. make at source directory
    %> cd $ASYMDIR/src
    %> make 
    %> make install (default install destination is $HOME/bin. create $HOME/bin in advance)
    
3. need run.db at analysis directory 
   see 00README.rundb for syntax (not yet available)

4. Executing Asym
    %> cd $ASYMDIR
    %> Asym -f 7069.101.data

    Try
    %> Asym -h for options
    
5. Outputs:

    hbookfile: outsampleex.hbook
    
    
6. Some utility to run Asym and histogram brawsing
   %> cd $ASYMDIR
   %> RHICAna.pl &

    Some directrories to be created
    $ASYMDIR/Hbooks                  : store hbook files
    $ASYMDIR/Log                     : offline log directory	   
    $ASYMDIR/ps                      : for postscript outputs
    Some useful paw macros and script for plotting
    $ASYMDIR/kumac/*.kumac,*.pl,*.sh : paw macro for plotting


